  {
    id: 'prompt-24',
    prompt: 'Establish a morning birding routine by setting aside 45 minutes every weekend to visit your chosen local hotspot at optimal times',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Creating a consistent birding schedule builds the foundation for developing serious observation skills and helps you understand seasonal patterns at a familiar location. Regular visits to the same spot allow you to track changes in bird populations, notice subtle behavioral patterns, and build familiarity with individual birds and their territories. This routine practice develops the patience and attention to detail essential for advanced birding while ensuring you maintain momentum in building your identification skills.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-25',
    prompt: 'Create a comprehensive pre-trip preparation checklist including weather forecast review, gear inspection, and target species research for each birding outing',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Systematic preparation before each birding trip maximizes your observation opportunities by ensuring you\'re equipped for conditions and focused on realistic targets for the season and location. Checking weather helps you dress appropriately and anticipate how conditions might affect bird activity, while researching recent sightings and seasonal patterns helps you know what to look for. This preparation routine transforms casual outings into strategic birding sessions that build your skills more effectively.'
  },
  {
    id: 'prompt-26',
    prompt: 'Research and plan your first seasonal birding strategy by identifying which months offer the best opportunities for migration viewing in your region',
    category: 'planning',
    helpText: 'Understanding migration timing is crucial for maximizing your birding success and helps you plan your most exciting and productive outings around peak movement periods. Spring and fall migrations bring the greatest diversity of species through most regions, with specific timing varying by location and bird families. Planning your birding calendar around these natural events ensures you don\'t miss the brief windows when rare or seasonal species are most likely to appear in your area.'
  }
];</parameter>
