    helpText: 'Learning to use bird call playback effectively can dramatically improve your birding success by attracting secretive species that might otherwise remain hidden in dense vegetation. However, ethical use requires limiting playback sessions to 30 seconds per species and avoiding repeated use in the same area to prevent stressing birds or disrupting their natural behaviors. This technique is particularly valuable during migration periods when proper timing and restraint can reveal species that would be impossible to observe through passive watching alone.'
  }</parameter>
