  {
    id: 'prompt-43',
    prompt: 'Set up and maintain a natural bird water source in your yard or balcony using a shallow dish, dripper, or small fountain to attract and observe birds daily',
    category: 'action',
    helpText: 'Providing a reliable water source is one of the most effective ways to attract diverse bird species for close observation, as birds need water for drinking and bathing regardless of the season. A shallow water feature (1-2 inches deep) with a gentle dripper or fountain creates movement and sound that draws birds from surprising distances, often attracting species that don\'t visit feeders. Maintaining fresh, clean water daily establishes your space as a trusted resource for local birds and provides consistent opportunities to study behavior, identify species, and practice your observation skills in a controlled environment.'
